HEADWORD: Intimacy
<hw>In"ti*ma*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Intimacies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[From
<er>Intimate</er>.]</ety> <def>The state of being intimate; close
familiarity or association; nearness in friendship.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Acquaintance; familiarity; fellowship;
friendship. See <er>Acquaintance</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

